		<h1>Setting Up External Sources</h1>
		<hr class="hr"/>
		<h3>Gmail</h3>
		<p>You'll need a gmail email account. Provide your email login and password. Both will be encrypted and stored in a secure database. The app will grab information about your recent email messages-- not the content, but just dates and recipients.</p>
		<h3>LinkedIn</h3>
		<p>Provide your LinkedIn email address and password. Again, both will be encrypted and securely stored. We'll fetch info about all your invitations and messages -- your private, one-on-one communications.</p>
		<h3>Verizon</h3>
		<p>For phone and text comms, the app will log into your account to get info about your call and SMS/MMS history. Verizon is delayed by up to a day in some cases. You will need to know your login information for the primary account holder. It might not be you. You will also need to know the answer to the secret question posed to the primary account holder when logging in. Like all other sensitive data, the app encrypts this and safely protects it.</p>
